erPublicProfile?gid=iradin@themagicianstower>Iradin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(1/10/03 12:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8413.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Having to Be Anon When I Go Home</span><hr size=1> This is going to make me sound very cheap and capitalistic but I can't stand beggars.  Not in real life of course but I can't go back to Felwithe with out having at least 20 tells sent to me.  I have been playing for about a year so I'm still kind of new but when I was a newb I didn't ask anybody for plat or armor.  It wouldn't even bother me as much if some of these people would ask.  I had one person tell me to give her money for her spells.  I responded that I had no money.  It was true at the time until recently I hadn't had more then 750 in the bank and most of that was ear marked for my spells and to save up for boots.  She shouted out to the zone that I was a cheap bastard.  <br>
    Has begging always been part of the game and I just didn't catch on or is it something new?  <br>
    I hope I am not the only one that is irked by this.  I don't mind helping newbies out.  I was helped out myself but I didn't ask.  I usually try to find the one Mage that doesn't send me a tell and buy him is next two or three sets of spells and outfit him with some of my spare gear.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=avalonatp>Avalona TP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#333333>(1/10/03 12:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8413.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.datazap.net/free/morbid_pleasure/avasm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Having to Be Anon When I Go Home</span><hr size=1> Amen, Iradin.<br>
<br>
I just started playing again this week after a very long break. I hadn't been on more than 2 minutes and I had a beggar working me for loot for his SK. When I told him I had nothing for melee he asked me if he rerolled to a mage if I'd give him loot. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I guess the days of earning your own stuff from having nothing is a lost art. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=252560"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.swbell.net/alaida/avasig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.guardiansofvalour.com/">Guardians of Valour</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valaglar>Valaglar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#333333>(1/10/03 1:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8413.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Having to Be Anon When I Go Home</span><hr size=1> I too despise beggars.  My policy is to never ever encourage beggars, and I let them know exactly that.  I give stuff away on a regular basis, and actually tend to do it more often in Greater Fay due to finding true newbies there so frequently.  Remember, the manual does actually encourage begging <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But, your encounter probably a professional beggar which is very sad.<br>
